Daily menu of an obese child: not breakfast and dinner stuffed
More than one third of children between the ages of 9 and 13 have overweight problems, where overweight affects 9 per cent of the school population and 5 per cent obesity.
Obese children come in most families with an unhealthy lifestyle, as is the case with current research.
It is demonstrated again the importance of the environment where it grows for a healthy development of the person, as well as the models that serve as reference.
At the table, obsessive children are fed, for example, by bottling at least twice as often as children of normal weight families.
For dinner, more than 19% of obese people had eaten fried potatoes the day before the analysis, which is linked to the prevention program "Obesity is not a coincidence".
In families of overweight children there is no habit of sports, which applies to most current families, where only 15 per cent of children responded that their parents, at least once a week, find time for physical exercise.
Survey of 900 children
The survey was conducted at the end of last school year and participated in the same nearly 900 basic education children from all over Czechia.
It was already the second edition of the program "Obesity is not a coincidence", which supports the General Health Insurance Company and the Unilever company.
So far, more than 12,000 children have participated in the project from the 4th to the 8th course.
A proper diet and quite exercise in the family are determining factors, which significantly reduce the number of overweight and even obesity children.
"Only half of the children surveyed have responded that they have five meals a day according to the regime: breakfast, lunch, food, merrienda and dinner, which is one of the basic conditions for a healthy diet," one of the results of the survey.
No breakfast but with ink for dinner
Experts warn that, in a healthy development, details are also important, which also count, such as having a set time for family breakfast.
In Czechia, however, only 23 per cent of school families have breakfast at the same time.
In most families, each one has breakfast alone.
But the worst thing was to find out that in 10 percent of the homes there is no breakfast.
Breakfast is, however, the basis of a correct daily diet.
The study shows that the families of obese children are much more often consumed by the sick potato fries.
Almost all - regardless of weight - drink daily sweet drinks (70%).
In general, more than 40 per cent of the children surveyed do sport, however, among their parents this result is reduced to less than half, only 15 per cent.
Make your diet
The next phase of the study enabled selected boys (204 boys and 172 girls from 13 schools) to create their own diets from all possible offers according to their tastes and opinions.
"The food preferences of Czech children between 12 and 15 years of age, from a healthy diet point of view, are far from ideal."
Among its favorite foods are pasta, meat and sweets
"The popularity of sweet drinks is particularly alarming," the final report of the study warns.
As the main food is carried the pasta and follows closely the poultry meat.
Practically, children always reject legume and taste for fish and vegetables is very low.
Change to healthy habits
At the same time, the study shows that children are willing to change their eating habits if they receive fair information.
"In the control group of the participants in the study, who completed the questionnaire after the end of the prevention program "Obesity is not a coincidence," in many cases a significant change was made in favour of the principles of healthy diet," points to the results of the study.
Call attention, for example, to the matter of sweet drinks, where many children would begin to prefer normal and common water.
Children would also choose poultry meat and fish for the main meal more frequently in the questionnaire and restrict the consumption of sweet food and flour derivatives.
