In Need for Speed: The Run competes all over America.
Review
A trip, in principle carefree, is complicated by a series of improper neglects of a routine trip during the morning shift.
To some extent, expectations were met, but that was useless if, in fact, nothing was intended to be done.
The new delivery, to which The Run is added, aroused great expectations before its premiere.
I promised that I would give new air to the old racing saga Need for Speed and, after shown, appears as a game that should not end up being a genre of action again without more.
We also feel curious about how the scenes would stay inserted, where the main character descends from the car and walks by his own foot.
As often happens in the NFS series, the results don't vary much about what we expected.
There are careers that can be made acceptable, but in the total calculation points are lost due to absurd errors, which have already appeared in the series for years.
Indeed, mistakes cannot be called, but rather, they are the incomprehensible release of programmers.
The adventure begins very well.
You are introduced into a story, whose protagonist, Jack, has certain personal problems; to solve them, you are offered to participate in an illegal career throughout America.
You sit on the wheel on the west coast, in San Francisco, and your mission is to get the first to New York.
The idea is to offer something interesting.
The route is divided into ten stages and then into more than fifty races.
It follows that each race takes place on a different route and the stages are located in different environments, which are quite diverse and interesting.
Thus, one does not feel remotely that the game always offers the same.
Some of the environments are even pleasant to the eye, although the technical level of the graph is equivalent to the previous delivery of the series.
So it's nothing from the other world.
But the stroll through the desert, the autumn landscape or the high snow-covered mountains produce a very pleasant visual effect.
In addition, racing is sometimes diversified by an atypical element.
So, for example, in the desert you find a sandstorm that decreases visibility.
On the other hand, in the mountains you must be careful not to bury an avalanche.
According to that, each of the races is very well developed.
There's only a couple of models, but that's enough.
For a moment, you try to advance to a number of required rivals (the normal thing in a classic race), then try to earn time (the classic timed duel) and then wait a duel against a single opponent.
In the midst of all this, sometimes the police, which only makes things even more difficult.
The novelty is the landscapes outside the car.
Interactive animations are presented when Jack, in most cases, has to escape from someone and you have to help him, always pressing the button right at the right time.
Nothing complicated.
It is surprising, however, that there are quite less landscapes in the game of what could be expected (in particular there are only three).
But the final result is positive, because this element does not become annoying and, in the context already mentioned, it is one of the elements that makes the game more interesting.
The driving model follows the tracks of previous episodes.
That means that today is no longer a great thing, but it cannot be said to be bad.
If you're looking for a realistic simulation, you can look elsewhere.
But a career designed with a lot of action is quite convenient for this driving style, although we can find something better between competition games.
So far, everything's in order.
But problems arise after a while.
Unlike the correct driving models, the same is no longer the case with collisions.
From games like this you can't expect to recreate deformations and complicated collisions, but in fact before a hit against any object, you can't predict how your car will react, which isn't everything in order.
It is typical that, by making a very adjusted advance or circulating the car with a normal traffic, there are only slight rocky, but in other almost identical situations, your car ends up making out of control.
Even it's completely destroyed.
Thanks to the resettling system, there are no great problems, but it can put you in a bad mood.
The resets are scheduled in such a way that, when you suffer from an accident or get out of the track, the game will return you to the last rescue point on the track.
However, only five resets are available in each race.
If you consume them all, you have to restart the race from the start.
So it's no more than a help in case something isn't right, but it's not very reliable.
Sometimes, nor does resettling help, only helps to learn the given stage of memory.
A great disadvantage of the game is that the same facts are repeated in different places.
In some curves, for example, you have to go in a specific way; otherwise, you cannot take it.
Other times you will find yourself in some "civil" vehicle site always with the same configuration, even if you are the first, fifth, or you arrive five minutes before or after.
This causes anger especially in situations, when you see that two cars that go to meet in opposite directions, your opponent advances smoothly, but when you arrive, you must either turn around or stop.
It's the same when you get here, because it's programmed that the "surprise" will always happen in front of your nose.
The opponents also have one more advantage.
Throughout the game you will reach places where, without taking into account the time, you will always advance the same opponent on the same site.
This also occurs at the end of the game, on a long bridge, which is even more shocking.
Your opponent must arrive before you, at any price.
When you go in front of you, it makes it difficult to see the cars coming from the front, so at first you can make the car pop.
You can understand the idea of creating a game with maximum doses of suspension and adrenaline, but the execution is so apparent that it will surely disappoint you immediately.
And it's a shame, because even if the travel model is simple, the game is fun and with action, so it's often not possible to follow in detail what happens or where.
And it really doesn't matter, if merit takes the idea with fifty exclusive clues or the ranking in the race so that it doesn't break the boredom, or anything else.
An unusual idea is the change of cars during racing.
You have to keep an eye on the gas dispensers next to the road, because that's exactly where you have to change cars, although in most cases you will have enough of what you have.
The cars are divided into three categories.
Sports are suitable for urban areas, American strong cars for straight highways and supersport exotics for technical driving, for example by mountain roads with curves.
In addition, the main narrative thread also appears a thread of parallel challenges, that is, there are races in specific places that you will know through the stories.
Here you will get not only medals, but also points of experience for your profile, which serves both challenges and stories.
Upon reaching the upper level, the driver opens several possibilities, starting with the car and ending with funds for the profile.
At the same time, an Autolog function is connected online, which compares your results with those of other players and provides other community functions.
One of the most difficult elements to understand is how the last race is made in history.
With the car you reach the subway tunnel (passe), where you run dark through the tracks (passe).
The speedometer marks you between 150 and 200 km/h (passe) and, suddenly, from behind you comes the subway convoy and you are carried forward without more.
In writing we will probably have a discussion about this for several days, about whether during the programming of the game no one thought even a little or whether the real authors take us for a panda of fools.
The technical part of the game is nothing extraordinary, but at least the overall visual effects result in most pleasant cases, sometimes even sovereign.
So what a pity it is that, at the most tense times, the quality of the image is reduced and, sometimes, in a serious way.
This mainly affects accidents where many participants are involved, when continuous image quality is no longer valid.
The audio is fine and the soundtrack is a matter of taste.
In order to please most of the youth group, the soundtrack belongs to the category "each one of his father and mother", but it can be assumed that no one would buy the game just for his music.
The final feeling of Need for Speed: The Run is therefore quite confused.
If the game were to avoid absolutely silly mistakes, we would have trouble claiming that The Run is the best NFS game in recent years.
It gives the feeling that the game is not over.
Fun is assured, but prepare because mistakes will hit you in the eyes with the strength of airport reflectors.
The choirs of the University of Carolina will participate in the concert "Students of Terciopelo".
The joint celebration of the International Student Day and the anniversary of the Third Party Revolution as a musical experience will take place for the third time at the Festival Festa Academica.
During the same period, twenty corals from secondary and university schools will be presented.
The festival revolves around two concerts on November 17.
"The University of Carolina has a high participation in the festival."
Among the current choirs are the choir of the Faculty of Pedagogy and the Faculty of Humanities, in the festival committee is the rector Václav Hampl," said the head of the organization, Jakub Čaloun.
The summit of the whole festival is the free entrance for all public at the high school choir concert, which will be held on 17 March at 14 a.m. in front of the National Technical Library in Dejvice.
The program has the participation of Czech jazz player Karel Rŏžička and his Celebration Jazz Mass.
In the evening the concert "Third Students" will be held at the venues of the Municipal House in Vynohrady, where university choirs will participate, including the choir of the Carolina Uninversity.
The academic festival aims not only to celebrate the International Student Day with dignity and to remember the 22nd anniversary of the Terciopelo Revolution, but also to present to the public coral music at the highest level and to promote collaborative creation among young people.
The main organizer is the Czech Union of Corals in collaboration with the Instituto de Secundaria Jan Kepler.
All the acts were supported by the mayor of Prague, Bohuslav Svoboda, and the rector of the University of Carolina, Václav Hampl.
The Festival will take place between 16 and 20 November between Prague and Pardubice.
The calendar offers, in addition to the concerts, a whole series of musical events, improvised shows of students and morning concerts.
More information can be found on the festival page www.festaacademica.cz
