Brand story:
The innovative IBM begins its second century of existence
If someone were looking for a term that would define the IBM strategy very precisely, the approximate one would be "long term".
For the general public, IBM is the symbol of a technological revolution, a company that is perceived as current and, however, has already been 100 years since its foundation.
The basis of this long-lasting character was put by the first head of the firm, visionary Thomas J. Watson Sr.
He already coined the motto that many problems in the world have a solution if people are willing to think.
His motto "Think!" became his seal, around which the life of the future giant will be built (it was also the title of an internal magazine that IBM started publishing in 1935).
Watson was also the basis of a carefully raised business culture.
