If the German model, based on renewable energies, is sometimes presented as an example, reality goes against such a discourse.
The Berlin election will entail an increase in the price of electricity, a greater dependence on energy due to the increased need for gas imported, in particular from Russia, an increase in CO2 emissions by the construction of gas and coal plants.
