Widely export-oriented, it covers a galaxy of SMEs specialized in international markets and can create non-movable jobs.
If France decided to abandon nuclear energy, it would mean the sacrifice of most of these SMEs and the loss of the €6 billion per year in French nuclear equipment and services exports.
What electrician would charge an EPR designed to operate sixty years, when the manufacturer's collapse is expected?
